    "answer": "To compare the concentration of 'Pure-Play' cybersecurity firms in the South-West (specifically Cork) against the National Average, we can look at the number of dedicated firms and the total number of cybersecurity offices.\n\n### Data Summary:\n- **Cork (South-West)**:\n  - Number of Offices (Dedicated Firms): **37**\n  - Total Number of Cyber Security Offices: **129**\n  \n- **National Average (Ireland)**:\n  - Number of Offices (Dedicated Firms): **191**\n  - Total Number of Cyber Security Offices: **734**\n\n### Concentration Calculation:\n1. **Cork Concentration**:\n   \\[\n   \\text{Cork Concentration} = \\frac{\\text{Dedicated Firms in Cork}}{\\text{Total Cyber Security Offices in Cork}} = \\frac{37}{129} \\approx 0.2876 \\text{ or } 28.76\\%\n   \\]\n\n2. **National Average Concentration**:\n   \\[\n   \\text{National Concentration} = \\frac{\\text{Dedicated Firms Nationally}}{\\text{Total Cyber Security Offices Nationally}} = \\frac{191}{734} \\approx 0.2604 \\text{ or } 26.04\\%\n   \\]\n\n### Conclusion:\n- **Cork's concentration of Pure-Play cybersecurity firms is approximately 28.76%**, while the **National Average is approximately 26.04%**. This indicates that Cork has a slightly higher concentration of dedicated cybersecurity firms compared to the national average.\n\nThis data is sourced from:\n- Table on Cyber Security Offices (Table ID: table_8, Page 15)\n- Table on Services Offered (Table ID: table_11, Page 20)",
